'''Atari Democrat''', a phrase first popularized during the early 1980s, references both the [[video game]] company [[Atari]] and [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic legislators]] who suggested that the support and development of [[high tech]] and related businesses would stimulate the economy and create jobs.

==Definition==
The definition of an ''Atari Democrat'' varies. A 1984 article for the ''[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]],'' defined the term as "a young [[Modern liberalism in the United States|liberal]] trying to push the party toward more involvement with high-tech solutions."<ref name="motherlode">{{Citation
