  | id =  }}</ref> It also noted that, "Since July 1982, it has appeared in the ''[[The New Yorker]]'', ''[[Business Week]]'', ''[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]'', ''[[Time]]'' and [...] in ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]''."<ref name="motherlode"/> A few years later, in 1989, ''[[The New York Times]]'' suggested that ''Atari Democrats'' (also known as ''Democrats' Greens'') are "young moderates who saw investment and high technology as the contemporary answer to the New Deal." <ref name=nytgreen>{{cite web
|url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=950DE3DF1430F937A25755C0A96F948260&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=print 
